matches stored vrf_request_key\n   195→  - Reads Orao randomness via `read_orao_randomness()` (rejects if unfulfilled)\n   196→  - Derives winning slot: `u64::from_le_bytes(randomness[0..8]) % total_entries`\n   197→  - Maps slot to winner: iterates players sequentially, cumulative entry count determines slot ownership\n   198→  - Validates `winner_account` matches derived winner (NotWinner error if wrong)\n   199→  - Calculates pool = entry_amount × total_entries, then `calculate_net_payout(pool)` → (fee, payout)\n   200→  - Transfers payout to winner + fee to treasury via `transfer_lamports_from_pda`\n   201→  - Emits `RoundSettled` event with full settlement data (tier, round_number, winner, randomness, winning_slot, total_entries, payout_amount, fee_amount, vrf_request_key)\n   202→  - Sets phase = Settled, claimed = true, stores winning_slot + winner\n   203→  - Account closed by Anchor's `close = round_creator` constraint (rent → creator)\n   204→- Platform CPI deferred to Phase B (game_type discriminator not yet added; with up to 20 players, remaining_accounts pattern needed)\n   205→- Registered module in `instructions/mod.rs` and added `claim_payout` to `lib.rs`\n   206→- Added test helpers: `setMockRandomness`, `getBalance`, `buildRandomness`, `deriveWinner`, `claimPayout`\n   207→- Added 7 bankrun tests:\n   208→  - Creator wins — correct payout and fee to treasury\n   209→  - Player2 wins — payout goes to player2 (creator triggers claim)\n   210→  - Multiple entries increases win probability proportionally (3:1 ratio)\n   211→  - Round PDA closed after claim (account no longer exists)\n   212→  - Rejects claim with unfulfilled randomness (RandomnessNotFulfilled)\n   213→  - Rejects claim with wrong winner_account (NotWinner)\n   214→  - Rejects claim when phase is not Locked (InvalidPhase)\n   215→\n   216→**Verification**: `anchor build -p lordofrngs` — **passed**. Tests pass separately:\n   217→- lordofrngs: 21 tests (14 existing + 7 new claim_payout)\